, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Gamboa","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Manuel, Luis, Carlos, Francisco, Jesus, Mario, Miguel, Pedro, Armando, Jaime.","Basque: topographic name composed of the elements <i>gain</i> ‘peak, summit’ + <i>boa</i> ‘rounded’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Sancho","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of uncertain origin, perhaps from Latin <i>sanctus</i> ‘holy’. It will always be associated with  Sancho Panza ,  Don Quixote's  companion."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Pérez","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Anglo-Norman: Anglo-Norman forms of Peter."],"variants":[{"name":"Perrez","meanings":["Anglo-Norman: Anglo-Norman forms of Peter."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1354684,"age":15,"year":"1200","julianDay":2159351,"description":"The Christian territory controlled the Kingdoms of Aragon, Navarre, and Castile.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sancho Pérez de Gamboa was born in 1185, in Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain, his father, Conde Pedro Vélez, VII Señor de Guevara Linaje de Vela, Conde de Alava, descendiente de la Casa Real de Navarra, de los Duques de Vasconia, de Aquitana y de Bretaña, was 28 and his mother, María Sáenz de Salcedo, Señora de Ayala Linaje de Ayala, descendiente de las Casas Reales de Navarra, de Aragón y de León y de los Señores de Vizcaya, was 27. He married Aldonza Diaz de Mena in 1217, in New Castile, Spain. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1185–":"1185–Surnud","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Su